A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing January 21, 2025, as Addiction Recovery Awareness Day; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, substance use disorders and mental illness affect millions of individuals of all
4 ages, races, and ethnic backgrounds as well as their families, friends, coworkers, and
5 communities; and
6 WHEREAS, more than 29 million Americans, including 900,000 Georgians, are building
7 lives in recovery from substance use disorders and mental illness; and
8 WHEREAS, recovery saves lives, restores families, strengthens communities, and builds a
9 stronger workforce, making Georgia a safer and healthier state; and
10 WHEREAS, peer-led recovery community organizations across our state continue to educate
11 the public and policy makers on the need for access to prevention, treatment, and peer-based
12 recovery support systems; and
13 WHEREAS, the voice of the recovery community is the single most important voice in the
14 recovery process; and
